info.headline: Flood Advisory issued April 28 at 6:15PM CDT until April 29 at 12:15AM CDT by NWS Duluth MN
info.description:
* WHAT...Small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...In Minnesota, Cook County.
* WHEN...Until 1215 AM CDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Water over roadways.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 615 PM CDT Monday, the public reported heavy rain in the advisory area due to thunderstorms and minor flooding of low water crossing. This is causing small stream flooding. Between 2 and 3 inches of rain have fallen. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Gunflint Lake, Sea Gull Lake, Saganaga Lake, Alpine Lake, Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness North of the Gunflint Trail, Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness, Winchell Lake, Long Island Lake, North Lake, Brule Lake, Poplar Lake, Cherokee Lake, Gneis Lake, Daniels Lake, Wine Lake, Bearskin Lake, Clearwater Lake, Watab Lake and Pine Lake. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

parameter.value: FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 1215 AM CDT TUESDAY
